* [[OSU-6162]] (PNU-9639; PNU-96391; PNU-96391A) – non-hallucinogenic serotonin 5-HT<sub>2A</sub> receptor partial agonist, dopamine D<sub>2</sub> receptor partial agonist, and sigma σ<sub>1</sub> receptor ligand (so-called "monoaminergic stabilizer") – bipolar depression, chronic fatigue syndrome, depressive disorders, stroke, subarachnoid hemorrhage, Parkinson's disease – Carlsson Research AB, Pfizer <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://adisinsight.springer.com/drugs/800008198|title=OSU 6162 - AdisInsight|website=adisinsight.springer.com}}</ref><ref name="CanalMorgan2012">{{cite journal | vauthors = Canal CE, Morgan D | title = Head-twitch response in rodents induced by the hallucinogen 2,5-dimethoxy-4-iodoamphetamine: a comprehensive history, a re-evaluation of mechanisms, and its utility as a model | journal = Drug Test Anal | volume = 4 | issue = 7–8 | pages = 556–576 | date = 2012 | pmid = 22517680 | pmc = 3722587 | doi = 10.1002/dta.1333 | url = | quote = Regardless, a more parsimonious explanation is that certain 5-HT2 receptor-activating compounds, such as DOI and psilocin, cause specific conformations of 5-HT2 receptors that lead to LSD-like psychedelic effects.[94,232] Moreover, although the 5-HT2 agonists mCPP, lorcaserin, and quipazine, are often considered 'non-hallucinogenic', they actually do produce perceptual, cognitive, and emotional changes that may be considered 'hallucinogenic'.[15,233,234] These effects, however, are generally not considered LSD-like. Finally, it is noteworthy that novel, partial 5-HT2A/D2 receptor agonists also attenuate the DOI-elicited HTR.[235,236]}}</ref><ref name="Mirchandani-DuqueChoucriHernández-Mondragón2024">{{cite journal | vauthors = Mirchandani-Duque M, Choucri M, Hernández-Mondragón JC, Crespo-Ramírez M, Pérez-Olives C, Ferraro L, Franco R, Pérez de la Mora M, Fuxe K, Borroto-Escuela DO | title = Membrane Heteroreceptor Complexes as Second-Order Protein Modulators: A Novel Integrative Mechanism through Allosteric Receptor-Receptor Interactions | journal = Membranes | volume = 14 | issue = 5 | date = April 2024 | page = 96 | pmid = 38786931 | pmc = 11122807 | doi = 10.3390/membranes14050096 | doi-access = free | url = | quote = This concept is also supported by experiments on OSU-6162, a selective Sigma 1R ligand in low doses [176]. This Sigma1R ligand produced in the nucleus accumbens shell substantial increases in the density of the D2R–Sigma1R and A2AR–D2R heterocomplexes, supporting the existence of A2AR–D2R–Sigma1R trimeric complexes in which the Sigma1R agonist can strongly enhance the antagonistic allosteric A2AR–D2R interaction. This mechanism may mediate the enhanced antagonistic A2AR–D2R interaction, causing marked inhibition of cocaine reward, leading to cocaine addiction.}}</ref><ref name="CarlssonBursteinKloberg2011">{{cite journal | vauthors = Carlsson ML, Burstein ES, Kloberg A, Hansson S, Schedwin A, Nilsson M, Rung JP, Carlsson A | title = I. In vivo evidence for partial agonist effects of (-)-OSU6162 and (+)-OSU6162 on 5-HT2A serotonin receptors | journal = J Neural Transm (Vienna) | volume = 118 | issue = 11 | pages = 1511–1522 | date = November 2011 | pmid = 21874578 | doi = 10.1007/s00702-011-0704-8 | url = }}</ref><ref name="BursteinCarlssonOwens2011">{{cite journal | vauthors = Burstein ES, Carlsson ML, Owens M, Ma JN, Schiffer HH, Carlsson A, Hacksell U | title = II. In vitro evidence that (-)-OSU6162 and (+)-OSU6162 produce their behavioral effects through 5-HT2A serotonin and D2 dopamine receptors | journal = J Neural Transm (Vienna) | volume = 118 | issue = 11 | pages = 1523–1533 | date = November 2011 | pmid = 21866391 | doi = 10.1007/s00702-011-0701-y | url = }}</ref><ref name="SahlholmÅrhemFuxe2013">{{cite journal | vauthors = Sahlholm K, Århem P, Fuxe K, Marcellino D | title = The dopamine stabilizers ACR16 and (-)-OSU6162 display nanomolar affinities at the σ-1 receptor | journal = Mol Psychiatry | volume = 18 | issue = 1 | pages = 12–14 | date = January 2013 | pmid = 22349783 | doi = 10.1038/mp.2012.3 | url = }}</ref><ref name="Borroto-EscuelaRomero-FernandezWydra2020">{{cite journal | vauthors = Borroto-Escuela DO, Romero-Fernandez W, Wydra K, Zhou Z, Suder A, Filip M, Fuxe K | title = OSU-6162, a Sigma1R Ligand in Low Doses, Can Further Increase the Effects of Cocaine Self-Administration on Accumbal D2R Heteroreceptor Complexes | journal = Neurotox Res | volume = 37 | issue = 2 | pages = 433–444 | date = February 2020 | pmid = 31782100 | pmc = 6989596 | doi = 10.1007/s12640-019-00134-7 | url = }}</ref>
